\begin{align*}
10 e^{2 \pi i/11} &= 10 \left(\cos \frac{2 \pi}{11} + i \sin \frac{2 \pi}{11}\right),\\
10 e^{15 \pi i/22} &= 10 \left(\cos \frac{15 \pi}{22} + i \sin \frac{15 \pi}{22}\right).
\end{align*}

Adding these two complex numbers, we get

\begin{align*}
10 e^{2 \pi i/11} + 10 e^{15 \pi i/22} &= 10 \left(\cos \frac{2 \pi}{11} + i \sin \frac{2 \pi}{11}\right) + 10 \left(\cos \frac{15 \pi}{22} + i \sin \frac{15 \pi}{22}\right)\\
&= 10 \left(\cos \left(\frac{2 \pi}{11} + \frac{15 \pi}{22}\right) + i \sin \left(\frac{2 \pi}{11} + \frac{15 \pi}{22}\right)\right)\\
&= 10 \left(\cos \frac{17 \pi}{22} + i \sin \frac{17 \pi}{22}\right).
\end{align*}

Therefore, the ordered pair $(r, \theta)$ is $\boxed{\left(10, \frac{17 \pi}{22}\right)}$. I hope it is correct.

