Dividing the second equation by $t$ (since $t$ is nonzero), we get
\begin{align*}
y - yt^2 &= 2.
\end{align*}
Subtracting this equation from the first equation, we have
\begin{align*}
x + xt^2 - (y - yt^2) &= 1 - 2,\\
x - y + (x + y)t^2 &= -1.
\end{align*}
